# Bakery Analytics — Project Overview

## Tech Stack
- Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript (strict)
- Supabase (auth, DB, RLS)
- @supabase/ssr for cookie-based auth
- SheetJS for Excel parsing (loaded from /public, NOT via import)
- Deployed on Vercel
- PWA enabled

## Project Structure
- `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` — Browser Supabase client
- `src/lib/supabase/server.ts` — Server Supabase client
- `src/lib/supabase/env.ts` — Decoded env constants (base64 → plain)
- `src/lib/loadXlsx.ts` — Safe SheetJS loader (from /public)
- `public/xlsx.full.min.js` — Pre-built SheetJS (DO NOT DELETE)

## Data Flow
- ALL data comes from Supabase via `useSupabaseData` hook
- `dataLoader.ts` has been removed — do not recreate it
- Cookie name for auth: `"hlaiyxpiebmvkb-auth-token"` — must match in ALL files
- Excel uploads: client-side parser, .xlsx format only

## AI Behavior Rules
- Respond in Hebrew when I write in Hebrew, code and comments in English
- Before making changes, explain what you plan to do
- Make minimal, focused changes — don't refactor unrelated code
- Never invent libraries or APIs that don't exist — verify first
- Always check existing code patterns before writing new code
- When unsure, ask — don't guess
